{"lemma":"أَخْنَس","slug":"أَخْنَس","root":"خ.ن.س","root_slug":"خ-ن-س","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ن-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11612"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%B3"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make go backwards, to make recede, to make stay behind, to keep back"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"camous, crooked in the nose"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wild bovine, gazelle"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root خ ن س (ḵ n s).\n\nFrom having a camous nose."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11612","headword_ar":"اَخْنَسُ","root":"xns","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having a camous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camoys, nose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the configuration termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xanasN","text_ar":"خَنَسٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the nose:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xanisa AlA^anofu","text_ar":"خَنِسَ الاَنْفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a nose of which the bone is short and the end turning back towards its bone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xanosaA='u","text_ar":"خَنْسَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xunosN","text_ar":"خُنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xanasN","text_ar":"خَنَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"in its original application is in gazelles and bulls and cows: (TA:) all bulls and cows are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xunos","text_ar":"خُنْس"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, TA,) and so are all gazelles: (TA:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xunusN","text_ar":"خُنُسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with two dammehs, (K,) but written by Sh"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xunosN","text_ar":"خُنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) is used to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gazelles:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulls"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xanosaA='u","text_ar":"خَنْسَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an epithet applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild cow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axonasu","text_ar":"اَخْنَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tick:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xin~awosN","text_ar":"خِنَّوْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) which last is an epithet so applied as relating to his face and his nose: (Fr, TA:) and the last, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xn~ws","text_ar":"خنّوس","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", is also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a young pig:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA:) or in this sense it is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Fr, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xanaAsN","text_ar":"خَنَاسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xin~awosN","text_ar":"خِنَّوْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xunosN","text_ar":"خُنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is metaphorically applied [as an"},{"kind":"page_break","n":817},{"kind":"text","text":"epithet] to arrows, in the following verse, describing a coat of mail:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lahaA EukanN tarud~u Aln~abola xunosFA\n                      \n                     \n                        watohozaA^u biA@lomaEaAbili waA@loqiTaAEi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It has folds which repel the arrows turned up at the points, and mock at the broad and long, and the small and broad, arrow-heads"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadamN xanosaA='u","text_ar":"قَدَمٌ خَنْسَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A foot flat in the hollow part of the sole, and fleshy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","A","Sgh","Fr","As"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}